Given: CD is the perpendicular bisector of AB
Prove: AC ∼=CB
TABLE 5.1:
Statement Reason
1. 1.
2. D is the midpoint of AB 2.
3. 3. Definition of a midpoint
4. 6 CDA and 6 CDB are right angles 4.
5. 6 CDA∼= 6 CDB 5.
6. 6. Reflexive PoC
7. 4CDA∼=4CDB 7.
8. AC ∼=CB 8.
